name: contemporary colors for the bewildered hearts

metadata.name: all of my friends
metadata.description:
all of my friends by suhasini khattar

we paint passionately everything, but our own desolately chaotic canvas. she sings of her dependence on careful strings of attachment defining her worth. she realises there is no such thing as good influence, as their actions and opinions mold her away from herself. yet struggling with her identity, she calls out to be held, to be embraced for all her cluelessness.
